 Airtel Office  Airtel said the new 0901 number range, which brings its numbering series scheme to eight, would offer more Nigerians an opportunity to experience seamless telephony/mobile Internet service on an innovative and affordable network with expansive 4G coverage. Chief Commercial Officer, Airtel Nigeria, Dinesh Balsingh, who spoke on the development yesterday, said the telco had been positioned as the network of first choice for voice calls and mobile Internet and the introduction of a new number series is an affirmation that it enjoys the confidence and support of many telecoms consumers across the country. The firm currently has the following numbering series: 0802, 0808, 0708, 0812, 0701, 0902, and 0901. To enable commenting and other interactive features, please switch to the more advanced .